    "number": 2512,
    "state": "closed",
    "state_reason": "completed",
    "title": "Allow force-rebroadcasting of a transaction, make sendrawtransaction return a unique message if transaction is already known",
    "body": "At the moment, if you want to rebroadcast a transaction, say, to a new node, you need to getrawtransaction, take the output of that, and use it with sendrawtransaction after restarting the client. If you try this without the restart, you'll get this: \"TX rejected (code -22)\"\nIf a transaction is already in the client's memory, it should return a more specific error message, the way \"transaction already in block chain (code -5)\" is returned for one of those transactions. In addition, there should be a way to force a rebroadcast, whether that's simply making a would-be rebroadcast go through rather than rejecting, or adding a command that will push it through anyway.\n",
